  "lyrics": "Don't bring me down Let the light lift you Don't bring me down Look at what you have found Listen to the sound Listen to the sound Of everything you have found When you look up And when you look down Don't drown Don't bring me down I say yeah I say yeah Don't bring me down Every day and night I've seen many types of knots And many lives evolved When many top you top it over like a parking lot You got grass all over the earth Concrete degraded just fine Cemeteries lost in like and lost in love without you Yeah I'd be lost in life and lost in life without you Don't bring me down Hope and remember everything you have found Ella Come on baby now Don't bring me down Yeah yeah I say Ella Don't bring me down I look to my left and look to my right And I see the love of my life It never fails when I look to his heart That's why Yeah That's why I say baby don't bring me down Don't bring us down Don't bring me down Lost in time Lost away Can't talk with you But I would say yes Don't bring me down Lost in time Lost in mind No I can't talk about the lost in mind I know you can't just walk away Please have a stop Even just partially Hangin' on this axis Listen to the sounds",
